    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1598918,
      "reputation" : 31306,
      "user_id" : 1480391,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 59,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/JbyYH.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Yves M.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1480391/yves-m"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 172,
    "last_activity_date" : 1614691145,
    "last_edit_date" : 1614691145,
    "creation_date" : 1410157625,
    "answer_id" : 25718495,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Up to date and complete answer with Jackson 2</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Using Annotation</h2>\n<pre><code>import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnoreProperties;\n\n@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)\npublic class MyMappingClass {\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-annotations/javadoc/2.6/com/fasterxml/jackson/annotation/JsonIgnoreProperties.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JsonIgnoreProperties</a> on Jackson online documentation.</p>\n<h2>Using Configuration</h2>\n<p>Less intrusive than annotation.</p>\n<pre><code>import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectReader;\n\nObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\nobjectMapper.configure(DeserializationFeature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false);\n\nObjectReader objectReader = objectMapper.reader(MyMappingClass.class);\nMyMappingClass myMappingClass = objectReader.readValue(json);\n</code></pre>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-databind/javadoc/2.6/com/fasterxml/jackson/databind/DeserializationFeature.html#FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES\" rel=\"noreferrer\">FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES</a> on Jackson online documentation.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2024994,
      "reputation" : 468,
      "user_id" : 1810439,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/99ccce0dc0bb63df5034e1d2e067f8f7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "mekdev",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1810439/mekdev"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1411757389,
    "creation_date" : 1411757389,
    "answer_id" : 26066382,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As stated above the annotations only works if this is specified in the parent POJO class and not the class where the conversion from JSON to Java Object is taking place.</p>\n\n<p>The other alternative without touching the parent class and causing disruptions is to implement your own mapper config only for the mapper methods you need for this.</p>\n\n<p>Also the package of the Deserialization feature has been moved.\nDeserializationConfig.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES to\nDeserializationConfig.Feature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES</p>\n\n<pre><code>import org.codehaus.jackson.map.DeserializationConfig;\n...\nobjectMapper.configure(DeserializationConfig.Feature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7407636,
      "reputation" : 281,
      "user_id" : 5636084,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cbf00ec2a050a56f2f3ed35eff003066?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "user5636084",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5636084/user5636084"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 28,
    "last_activity_date" : 1449172632,
    "last_edit_date" : 1449172632,
    "creation_date" : 1449162514,
    "answer_id" : 34072067,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If using a pojo class based on JSON response. If chances are there that json changes frequently declare at pojo class level:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and at the objectMapper add this if you are converting:</p>\n\n<pre><code>objectMapper.configure(DeserializationConfig.Feature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>So that code will not break.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1764320,
      "reputation" : 1851,
      "user_id" : 1610544,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Zoz6j.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Alboz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1610544/alboz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1481020085,
    "creation_date" : 1481020085,
    "answer_id" : 40993067,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Starting with Jackson version 2.4 and above there have been some changes.\nHere is how you do it now:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>..........................................................................</p>\n\n<pre><code> ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();\n    // to prevent exception when encountering unknown property:\n mapper.disable(DeserializationFeature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES);\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Note: The @annotation based solution remains the same so if you like to use that see the other answers.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><code>For more information see the 10 minutes Configuration tutorial at:</code> <a href=\"https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3428640,
      "reputation" : 1143,
      "user_id" : 2873710,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/CYuvL.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "inOut",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2873710/inout"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1482202631,
    "creation_date" : 1482202631,
    "answer_id" : 41234188,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'm using jackson-xxx 2.8.5.Maven Dependency like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;dependencies&gt;\n    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/jackson-core --&gt;\n    &lt;dependency&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;com.fasterxml.jackson.core&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;jackson-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.8.5&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;/dependency&gt;\n\n    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/jackson-annotations --&gt;\n    &lt;dependency&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;com.fasterxml.jackson.core&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;jackson-annotations&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.8.5&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;/dependency&gt;\n\n    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/jackson-databind --&gt;\n    &lt;dependency&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;com.fasterxml.jackson.core&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;jackson-databind&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.8.5&lt;/version&gt;\n    &lt;/dependency&gt;\n\n&lt;/dependencies&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>First,If you want ignore unknown properties globally.you can config <code>ObjectMapper</code>.<br>\nLike below:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\nobjectMapper.configure(DeserializationFeature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you want ignore some class,you can add annotation <code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)</code> on your class like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)\npublic class E1 {\n\n    private String t1;\n\n    public String getT1() {\n        return t1;\n    }\n\n    public void setT1(String t1) {\n        this.t1 = t1;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6699975,
      "reputation" : 5858,
      "user_id" : 5166818,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b55a266b4b6665c145653a39157d8004?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Amit Kaneria",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5166818/amit-kaneria"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 97,
    "last_activity_date" : 1502998634,
    "creation_date" : 1502998634,
    "answer_id" : 45743651,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>it can be achieved 2 ways:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Mark the POJO to ignore unknown properties</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)\n</code></pre></li>\n<li><p>Configure ObjectMapper that serializes/De-serializes the POJO/json as below:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ObjectMapper mapper =new ObjectMapper();            \n// for Jackson version 1.X        \nmapper.configure(DeserializationConfig.Feature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false);\n// for Jackson version 2.X\nmapper.configure(DeserializationFeature.FAIL_ON_UNKNOWN_PROPERTIES, false) \n</code></pre></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
