    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12985701,
      "reputation" : 398,
      "user_id" : 9386660,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-XdUIqdMkCWA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/4252rscbv5M/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Parul",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9386660/parul"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 36,
    "last_activity_date" : 1519146423,
    "last_edit_date" : 1519146423,
    "creation_date" : 1519142428,
    "answer_id" : 48889330,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = true)</code> \nworked well for me. I have a java application which runs on tomcat with jdk 1.7. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11221837,
      "reputation" : 2388,
      "user_id" : 8232755,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0dcf8dcbe0d3d9935bec93d5b380cc45?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Thoomas",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8232755/thoomas"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1536842695,
    "creation_date" : 1536842695,
    "answer_id" : 52314039,
    "question_id" : 5455014,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For whom are using Spring Boot, you can configure the default behaviour of Jackson by using the <code>Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder</code>.</p>\n\n<p>For example :</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Bean\npublic Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder configureObjectMapper() {\n    Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder oMapper = new Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder();\n    oMapper.failOnUnknownProperties(false);\n    return oMapper;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Then you can autowire the <code>ObjectMapper</code> everywhere you need it (by default, this object mapper will also be used for http content conversion).</p>\n"
  } ],
